data.text:
Biography

JEZ DIOR is a LA-native singer-songwriter and rapper whose discography across “The Funeral”, “Youthenasia” and “Handle with Care” chronicles his personal coming of age experiences with love, depression, mortality, substance abuse and eventual sobriety. Bridging hip-hop, alternative and pop, Jez Dior experienced his first Top 40 Rhythmic Radio hit with “Nobody Knows” featuring Jackson Guthy and loves to make music that feels he’s sharing his struggles and story as if speaking candidly right from a therapist’s couch. Arresting hearts with his cutting lyrics, raw spirit and real life narratives, Jez has collaborated with G-Eazy, Goody Grace, ROME, Elijah Blake, Olivver The Kid, Keith Varon, Chris Wallace and Cisco Adler among others.
